aas:langStringTextType.aas:text: A Part AsPlanned represents an item in the Catena-X Bill of Material (BOM) in As-Planned lifecycle status.

IEC61360:definition.IEC61360:langString: A Part AsPlanned represents an item in the Catena-X Bill of Material (BOM) in As-Planned lifecycle status.
Trait to ensure data format for Catena-X ID
The part ID is a multi-character string, ususally assigned by an ERP system
Part Name in string format from the respective system in the aas:value chain
A part type must be placed into one of the following classes: 'component', 'product', 'software', ‘assembly’, 'tool', or 'raw material'.
The characteristics of the part type
Describes a Property which contains the date and time with an optional timezone.
Describes a Property which contains the date and time with an optional timezone.

aas:langStringTextType.aas:text: A Part AsPlanned represents an item in the Catena-X Bill of Material (BOM) in As-Planned lifecycle status.
The fully anonymous Catena-X ID of the serialized part, valid for the Catena-X dataspace.
Encapsulation for data related to the part type

Part ID as assigned by the manufacturer of the part. The Part ID identifies the part (as designed) in the manufacturer`s dataspace. The Part ID does not reference a specific instance of a part and thus should not be confused with the serial number.
Name of the part as assigned by the manufacturer
The classification of the part type according to STEP standard definition
Start date of validity period
End date of validity period
